---
import ShowcaseLayout from "../../../../layouts/ShowcaseLayout.astro";

const recipe = "newsletter";

// Custom nav for newsletter - minimal editorial style
const navItems = [
  { label: "Archive", href: "#archive" },
  { label: "About", href: "#about" },
  { label: "FAQ", href: "#faq" },
];
---

<ShowcaseLayout
  title="The Weekly Spark - Ideas That Ignite"
  description="A curated newsletter delivering actionable insights on creativity, productivity, and personal growth every Wednesday."
  recipe={recipe}
>
  <!-- Custom Newsletter Header - Editorial Style -->
  <header class="newsletter-header">
    <div class="header-inner">
      <a href="#" class="header-logo">
        <span class="spark-icon">&#9733;</span>
        <span class="logo-text">The Weekly Spark</span>
      </a>
      <nav class="header-nav">
        {navItems.map((item) => (
          <a href={item.href} class="nav-link">{item.label}</a>
        ))}
      </nav>
      <a href="#subscribe" class="header-cta">Subscribe Free</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Hero: Sample Issue Preview Above Fold -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <div class="hero-text">
        <p class="issue-label">Latest Issue</p>
        <h1>The Art of Showing Up</h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">Why consistency beats intensity, and how to build habits that stick without burning out.</p>
        <div class="hero-meta">
          <span class="meta-date">December 11, 2024</span>
          <span class="meta-divider">&bull;</span>
          <span class="meta-read">5 min read</span>
        </div>
        <form class="hero-form">
          <input type="email" placeholder="Enter your email" class="hero-input" />
          <button type="submit" class="hero-button">Start Reading</button>
        </form>
        <p class="hero-proof">Join 12,400+ curious minds. Free forever.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-preview">
        <div class="preview-card">
          <div class="preview-header">
            <span class="preview-badge">This Week</span>
          </div>
          <div class="preview-content">
            <p class="preview-greeting">Hey there,</p>
            <p class="preview-text">
              Last week, I watched my 7-year-old learn to ride a bike. She fell
              <em>seventeen times</em> before making it across the driveway. By fall
              twelve, I was ready to call it quits. She wasn't.
            </p>
            <p class="preview-text">
              "I'm not done yet," she said, brushing off her knees.
            </p>
            <p class="preview-text">
              That moment stuck with me. When did we adults start believing that
              falling meant failing? When did we start demanding perfection from
              day one?
            </p>
            <p class="preview-text highlight">
              This week, I want to talk about the power of just showing up...
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="preview-fade"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Pillars - What You'll Get -->
  <section class="pillars-section">
    <div class="pillars-header">
      <h2>Every Wednesday, You'll Get</h2>
      <p class="pillars-subtitle">Curated ideas that respect your time and expand your thinking.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillars-grid">
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-number">01</div>
        <h3>One Big Idea</h3>
        <p>A deep dive into a concept that'll shift how you think about creativity, work, or life. No fluff, all substance.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-number">02</div>
        <h3>Three Quick Sparks</h3>
        <p>Curated links, quotes, and recommendations. Books, articles, tools, and ideas worth your attention.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-number">03</div>
        <h3>One Action Step</h3>
        <p>A simple, practical exercise you can try this week. Small experiments that lead to meaningful change.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Full Sample Issue - Scrollable -->
  <section class="sample-section" id="archive">
    <div class="sample-header">
      <h2>Read a Full Issue</h2>
      <p class="sample-subtitle">See exactly what lands in your inbox every Wednesday.</p>
    </div>
    <article class="sample-issue">
      <header class="issue-header">
        <div class="issue-masthead">
          <span class="spark-icon small">&#9733;</span>
          <span>The Weekly Spark</span>
        </div>
        <p class="issue-date">Issue #127 &bull; December 4, 2024</p>
      </header>

      <div class="issue-content">
        <h1 class="issue-title">The Myth of Work-Life Balance</h1>

        <p class="issue-greeting">Hey there,</p>

        <p>For years, I chased the mythical work-life balance. I imagined it as a
        perfectly calibrated scale: work on one side, life on the other, both
        hovering in perfect equilibrium.</p>

        <p>Spoiler: it doesn't exist.</p>

        <p>Not because you're doing it wrong. But because the metaphor itself is
        broken. Balance implies a static state. Life isn't static. It's <em>dynamic</em>.</p>

        <p>Some weeks, a project demands your full attention. Some weeks, family
        needs you. Some weeks, <em>you</em> need you. Trying to maintain perfect
        balance in all of this is like trying to hold a yoga pose during an
        earthquake.</p>

        <blockquote class="issue-quote">
          "Instead of balance, think rhythm. Life isn't a scale. It's a dance."
        </blockquote>

        <p>Here's what I've learned: instead of balance, aim for <strong>integration</strong>.
        Instead of separating work and life into competing boxes, look for where
        they can reinforce each other.</p>

        <p>The question isn't "how do I balance everything?" It's "what does a
        sustainable rhythm look like for me, right now, in this season?"</p>

        <div class="issue-divider">
          <span>&#9733;</span>
          <span>&#9733;</span>
          <span>&#9733;</span>
        </div>

        <h2>Three Sparks This Week</h2>

        <div class="spark-item">
          <span class="spark-number">1.</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Read:</strong> Cal Newport's new piece on
            <a href="#">Slow Productivity</a> is a manifesto for sustainable work.
            Key insight: work at a natural pace, not a manufactured one.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="spark-item">
          <span class="spark-number">2.</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Try:</strong> The "energy audit." For one week, note when you
            feel energized vs. drained. Patterns will emerge. Adjust accordingly.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="spark-item">
          <span class="spark-number">3.</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Listen:</strong> This interview with <a href="#">Esther Perel</a>
            on reimagining relationships with work hit different. "We've made work
            our primary relationship."
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="issue-divider">
          <span>&#9733;</span>
          <span>&#9733;</span>
          <span>&#9733;</span>
        </div>

        <h2>Your Action This Week</h2>

        <div class="action-box">
          <p><strong>The "Good Enough" List</strong></p>
          <p>Pick three things this week where "good enough" actually is good enough.
          Not everything needs to be exceptional. Sometimes, done beats perfect.</p>
          <p class="action-prompt">Reply to this email with your three things. I read every response.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="issue-signoff">
          <p>Until next Wednesday,</p>
          <p class="signoff-name">Sarah</p>
          <p class="signoff-role">Curator, The Weekly Spark</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <!-- Reader Quotes - Integrated Throughout -->
  <section class="quotes-section">
    <div class="quotes-header">
      <h2>What Readers Say</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="quotes-grid">
      <blockquote class="reader-quote featured">
        <p>"The only newsletter I actually look forward to reading. It's like a
        thoughtful conversation with a wise friend, delivered to my inbox."</p>
        <cite>
          <span class="cite-name">Michael T.</span>
          <span class="cite-detail">Reading since Issue #12</span>
        </cite>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote class="reader-quote">
        <p>"Short, insightful, and genuinely useful. I've implemented at least a
        dozen ideas from The Weekly Spark into my daily routine."</p>
        <cite>
          <span class="cite-name">Elena K.</span>
          <span class="cite-detail">Product Designer</span>
        </cite>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote class="reader-quote">
        <p>"Finally, a newsletter that respects my time. No BS, no filler, just
        good thinking delivered consistently."</p>
        <cite>
          <span class="cite-name">David L.</span>
          <span class="cite-detail">Entrepreneur</span>
        </cite>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote class="reader-quote">
        <p>"Sarah has this gift for articulating things I've felt but couldn't put
        into words. Every issue feels personal."</p>
        <cite>
          <span class="cite-name">Amanda R.</span>
          <span class="cite-detail">Writer & Coach</span>
        </cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About the Curator - Editorial Style -->
  <section class="about-section" id="about">
    <div class="about-content">
      <div class="about-image">
        <div class="image-placeholder">
          <span class="image-initials">S</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <p class="about-label">Meet Your Curator</p>
        <h2>Sarah Mitchell</h2>
        <p class="about-bio">
          I spent 15 years in corporate marketing, climbing the ladder everyone
          told me to climb. I hit every milestone: promotions, corner office,
          the whole deal. And I was miserable.
        </p>
        <p class="about-bio">
          Three years ago, I left to figure out what actually matters. The Weekly
          Spark is what I learned along the way: weekly reflections on work,
          creativity, and building a life that fits.
        </p>
        <p class="about-bio">
          I live in Portland with my husband, two kids, and a dog who has more
          followers than I do. When I'm not writing, I'm probably overthinking
          my coffee order.
        </p>
        <div class="about-links">
          <a href="#" class="about-link">Twitter/X</a>
          <a href="#" class="about-link">LinkedIn</a>
          <a href="#" class="about-link">Email</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ - Accordion Style -->
  <section class="faq-section" id="faq">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <h2>Common Questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>How often will I hear from you?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Once a week, every Wednesday at 7am EST. That's it. No surprise emails,
          no promotional blasts, no "just checking in" messages. Your inbox is
          sacred and I respect that.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Is it really free?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes, completely free. The Weekly Spark will always have a free edition.
          I may introduce a paid tier in the future with bonus content, but the
          core newsletter will remain free forever.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What if I want to unsubscribe?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>One click, every email. No guilt trips, no "are you sure?" popups.
          If it's not serving you, I'd rather you leave than stay out of obligation.
          No hard feelings, ever.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Do you share my email with anyone?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Never. Your email is between us. I don't sell data, rent lists, or
          do any of that sketchy stuff. I use a privacy-focused email platform
          and take data protection seriously.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I reply to the newsletter?</span>
          <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Please do! Every reply comes directly to my inbox and I read every
          single one. Some of my best ideas have come from reader conversations.
          I might not respond to everything, but I read everything.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA - Simple and Clean -->
  <section class="final-cta-section" id="subscribe">
    <div class="cta-content">
      <h2>Join 12,400+ Curious Minds</h2>
      <p>One email. Every Wednesday. Ideas that stick.</p>
      <form class="cta-form">
        <input type="email" placeholder="Your email address" class="cta-input" />
        <button type="submit" class="cta-button">Subscribe</button>
      </form>
      <p class="cta-note">Free forever. Unsubscribe anytime.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Custom Newsletter Footer - Minimal Editorial -->
  <footer class="newsletter-footer">
    <div class="footer-inner">
      <div class="footer-brand">
        <span class="spark-icon small">&#9733;</span>
        <span class="footer-name">The Weekly Spark</span>
      </div>
      <p class="footer-tagline">Ideas that ignite, delivered weekly.</p>
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="#">Archive</a>
        <a href="#">About</a>
        <a href="#">Privacy</a>
        <a href="#">Unsubscribe</a>
      </div>
      <p class="footer-copyright">&copy; 2024 The Weekly Spark. Made with intention in Portland.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</ShowcaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ==========================================================================
     Newsletter Recipe - Editorial Typography & Warm Paper Aesthetic
     ========================================================================== */

  :root {
    --nl-bg: #FDFBF7;
    --nl-bg-warm: #F8F5EF;
    --nl-text: #2C2C2C;
    --nl-text-muted: #6B6B6B;
    --nl-accent: #2D6A4F;
    --nl-accent-light: #40916C;
    --nl-border: #E8E4DC;
    --nl-card-bg: #FFFFFF;
    --nl-serif: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif;
    --nl-sans: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
  }

  /* ==========================================================================
     Custom Header
     ========================================================================== */

  .newsletter-header {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    background: var(--nl-bg);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--nl-border);
  }

  .header-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .header-logo {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--nl-text);
  }

  .spark-icon {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--nl-accent);
  }

  .spark-icon.small {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .logo-text {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .header-nav {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .nav-link {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .nav-link:hover {
    color: var(--nl-text);
  }

  .header-cta {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    background: var(--nl-accent);
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .header-cta:hover {
    background: var(--nl-accent-light);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .header-nav {
      display: none;
    }

    .header-inner {
      padding: 0.875rem 1rem;
    }
  }

  /* ==========================================================================
     Hero Section - Sample Issue Preview
     ========================================================================== */

  .hero-section {
    padding: calc(80px + 4rem) 2rem 4rem;
    background: var(--nl-bg);
  }

  .hero-content {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .issue-label {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--nl-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .hero-section h1 {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--nl-text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-meta {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .meta-divider {
    margin: 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .hero-form {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-input {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 0.875rem 1rem;
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--nl-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: white;
  }

  .hero-input:focus {
    outline: none;
    border-color: var(--nl-accent);
  }

  .hero-button {
    padding: 0.875rem 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    background: var(--nl-accent);
    color: white;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition: background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .hero-button:hover {
    background: var(--nl-accent-light);
  }

  .hero-proof {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
  }

  /* Preview Card */
  .preview-card {
    background: var(--nl-card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--nl-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .preview-header {
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--nl-border);
  }

  .preview-badge {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--nl-accent);
  }

  .preview-content {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    max-height: 300px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .preview-greeting {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--nl-text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .preview-text {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--nl-text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .preview-text.highlight {
    color: var(--nl-accent);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .preview-fade {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 80px;
    background: linear-gradient(transparent, var(--nl-card-bg));
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero-content {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .hero-section h1 {
      font-size: 2.25rem;
    }

    .hero-form {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }

  /* ==========================================================================
     Content Pillars
     ========================================================================== */

  .pillars-section {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    background: var(--nl-bg-warm);
  }

  .pillars-header {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .pillars-header h2 {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--nl-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pillars-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
  }

  .pillars-grid {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .pillar {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .pillar-number {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--nl-accent);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .pillar h3 {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--nl-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pillar p {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pillars-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .pillar {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }

  /* ==========================================================================
     Full Sample Issue
     ========================================================================== */

  .sample-section {
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    background: var(--nl-bg);
  }

  .sample-header {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .sample-header h2 {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--nl-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .sample-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
  }

  .sample-issue {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: var(--nl-card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--nl-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .issue-header {
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--nl-border);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .issue-masthead {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .issue-date {
    font-family: var(--nl-sans);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
  }

  .issue-content {
    padding: 2.5rem 2rem;
  }

  .issue-title {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--nl-text);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .issue-greeting {
    font-family: var(--nl-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--nl-text-muted);
